Marketing Brief -- A.H. Belo Corp.:
   Company Posts 54% Decline
   In Fourth-Quarter Earnings
The company reported fourth-quarter revenue of $121.4
million, an increase of 2.6% from the same period a year
earlier. For the fourth quarter of 1990, the company reported
net income of $12.8 million, or 67 cents a share, on revenue
of $118.2 million.
   For the year, Belo said its net income was $12.4 million,
or 65 cents a share, on revenue of $431.6 million. For 1990,
the company reported net income of $29.6 million, or $1.55 a
share, on revenue of $439.1 million.